Navigation
Name Rascal/Expressions/Values/Number/Division
Synopsis Division on numeric values.
Syntax Exp1 / Exp2
Types
Exp1 Exp2 Exp1 / Exp2
int int int
int real real
real real real
Description Yields the result of dividing the value of NumExp1 by the value of NumExp2.
Examples 
rascal>12 / 3
int: 4
rascal>10 / 3
int: 3
rascal>12 / 3.0
real: 4.
rascal>10 / 3.0
real: 3.333333333
rascal>12 / 0
|stdin:///|(5,1,<1,5>,<1,6>): ArithmeticException("/ by zero")
